On Wed, 29 Oct 2003, Faster-Laster wrote:

> What I'm having trouble w/ is cutting the butt joints. I need to be
> able to (hopefully quickly) cut a simi-circle in the end of some of
> the tubes so that making a tee w/ two tubes is possible and close
> fitting before welding.

There is a tool used with aircraft tubing that holds the tubing in a jig
while using a fine-tooth hole saw to make the cut.  It even handles odd
angles.  You might check Aircraft Spruce or the Thomas Register for it.
Get back to me if you come up empty and I'll search my old Sport
Aviations.

George
